<div class="calcpad-output">
 <!-- Bilinear-style table lookup that chains 1D Hermite splines along both axes to interpolate a tabulated $T(i,\, j)$ surface.
<p>The canonical pattern for evaluating two-input design tables on intermediate values. -->
 <p>Input parameters</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>x</var>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   )  =
   <b>spline</b>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   ; 2; 4; 8 )
  </span>
  - x values
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>y</var>
   (
   <var>i</var>
   )  =
   <b>spline</b>
   (
   <var>i</var>
   ; 3; 9; 27 )
  </span>
  - y values
 </p>
 <p>Output values</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>R</var>
   <sub>1</sub>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   )  =
   <b>spline</b>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   ; 11; 12; 13 )
  </span>
  - first row
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>R</var>
   <sub>2</sub>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   )  =
   <b>spline</b>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   ; 21; 22; 23 )
  </span>
  - second row
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>R</var>
   <sub>3</sub>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   )  =
   <b>spline</b>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   ; 31; 32; 39 )
  </span>
  - third row
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>T</var>
   (
   <var>i</var>
   ;
   <var>j</var>
   )  =
   <b>spline</b>
   (
   <var>i</var>
   ;
   <var>R</var>
   <sub>1</sub>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   ) ;
   <var>R</var>
   <sub>2</sub>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   ) ;
   <var>R</var>
   <sub>3</sub>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   )  )
  </span>
  - complete table
 </p>
 <p>Calculation of interpolation factors</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>k</var>
   <sub>x</sub>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   )  =
   <span class="cond">$Root</span>
   {
   <var>x</var>
   (
   <var>j</var>
   )  =
   <var>x</var>
   ;
   <var>j</var>
   ∈ [1; 3]}
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>k</var>
   <sub>y</sub>
   (
   <var>y</var>
   )  =
   <span class="cond">$Root</span>
   {
   <var>y</var>
   (
   <var>i</var>
   )  =
   <var>y</var>
   ;
   <var>i</var>
   ∈ [1; 3]}
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>The interpolated function</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   ;
   <var>y</var>
   )  =
   <var>T</var>
   (
   <var>k</var>
   <sub>x</sub>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   ) ;
   <var>k</var>
   <sub>y</sub>
   (
   <var>y</var>
   )  )
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>Usage</p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   ( 2; 3 )  = 11
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   ( 5; 5 )  = 24.35
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   ( 4; 9 )  = 22
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   ( 8; 27 )  = 39
  </span>
 </p>
